\nrepresentation, we propose an analytical expression for the location of the\nhardness peak and show that at fixed precision, the number of constraints in\nthe integer program must increase with system size to yield truly hard\nproblems. The Wishart planted ensemble is interesting for its peculiar physical\nproperties and provides a useful and analytically-transparent set of problems\nfor benchmarking optimization algorithms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 1 Jun 2019 19:23:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 May 2020 20:34:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-06"}
