 (i.e. $G>0$),\nthough, changing Maxwell's into the BLTP law and assigning a bare rest mass to\nthe singularities is by itself not sufficient to obtain even a merely\nwell-defined joint initial value problem: the gravitational coupling also needs\nto be changed, conceivably in the manner of Jordan and Brans--Dicke.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 1 Jun 2019 23:18:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 Jun 2019 22:08:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 26 Jul 2019 15:32:18 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 16 Aug 2019 03:17:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
